DUKE UNIVERSITY HERBARIUM
297801

Galax urceolata (Poir.) Brummitt
(Galax aphylla auct. non L.)
det. R.L. Wilbur I. 2001
Duke University Herbarium

PLANTS OF NORTH CAROLINA
COLLECTED FOR THE HERBARIUM OF
DUKE UNIVERSITY

Galax aphylla L.

TRANSYLVANIA COUNTY: along state hwy. 215 about 1 mile
south of its intersection with the Blue Ridge Parkway.
Along the road, seepy cliff faces and rich oak
forest with heath understory on very steep slopes.
Elevation about 4000-4500 feet.

Very common in woods and along road. Leaves very
shiny, the older ones leathery. Flowers white, borne
on erect stalks.

Charlotte M. Taylor #1569                      12 June 1982


*Galax urceolata*
*Galax aphylla*
